    <summary>A Windows system tray application for monitoring and updating Chocolatey packages</summary>
    <description>
ChocoButler is a lightweight Windows system tray application that monitors your Chocolatey packages for updates and provides an easy way to install them.

## Features
- **System Tray Integration**: Runs quietly in the system tray
- **Automatic Monitoring**: Periodically checks for outdated packages
- **Visual Notifications**: Changes tray icon colour when updates are available
- **Easy Updates**: One-click package updates with administrator privileges
- **Individual Package Control**: Update specific packages or all at once
- **Settings Management**: Configure check intervals and notifications
- **Chocolatey Integration**: Works with existing Chocolatey installation

## Usage
After installation, ChocoButler will appear in your system tray.

- Right-click the icon to:
    - View outdated packages
    - Install updates
    - Check for updates manually
    - Access settings
    - Open Chocolatey GUI (if installed)
- Double-click the system tray icon to install updates.
- Click notifications to install updates.

## Requirements
- Windows 10/11
- .NET 8.0 Runtime
- Chocolatey package manager

